<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910625-0044</DOCNO><DOCID>910625-0044.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Fluor Corp.:   Contract for $220 Million   In Venezuela Goes to Unit</HL><DATE>06/25/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A3</SO><CO>   C.PDV FLR</CO><MS>ENERGY (ENE)INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>HEAVY CONSTRUCTION; INDUSTRIAL AND COMMERCIAL (CON)OIL, INTEGRATED MAJORS (OIL)PETROLEUM (PET)</IN><NS>PETROLEUM MARKET (PET)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)SOUTH AMERICA (SM)UNITED STATES (US)VENEZUELA (VE)</RE><LP>   Fluor Corp.'s Fluor Daniel Inc. unit said it received a$220 million engineering and construction contract from anaffiliate of Venezuela's national oil company to expand thelarge Amuay refinery in the town of Judibana.   Fluor Daniel, of Irvine, Calif., said the new Petroleos deVenezuela facility, called a delayed coker, will convertheavy oil into blending components for gasoline, diesel andjet fuel. The project, set for completion in mid-1993,includes a coke conveyor, loading dock, water-treatmentfacility and related common facilities.</LP><TEXT>   Fluor Daniel said its presence in Venezuela dates back tothe 1960s. In the early 1980s, Fluor received a $1.1 billioncontract to upgrade the Amuay refinery. The latest contractis the first announced by Fluor Daniel related to Venezuela'splanned $30 billion to $35 billion investment in its oilindustry between now and 1996, Fluor said.</TEXT></DOC>